EDITORS COMMENTS

This print showcases the elegant and regal Portrait of Princess Dagmar of Denmark, Maria Feodorovna of Russia. Taken in 1873, this fine art image captures the beauty and grace of a prominent member of the Romanov dynasty. The photograph is part of the esteemed collection at the Russian State Film and Photo Archive in Krasnogorsk. Princess Dagmar, also known as Maria Feodorovna, was born in 1847 and went on to become Tsarina Maria Feodorovna when she married Alexander III. This lithographic portrait perfectly encapsulates her poise and sophistication, highlighting her role as a prominent figure within the House of Romanov. The photographer behind this masterpiece is Charles Karl Bergamasco (1830-1896), whose skillful eye captured every detail with precision. His expertise shines through in this timeless portrait that has stood the test of time. As we gaze upon this remarkable piece, we are transported back to a bygone era where royalty reigned supreme. It serves as a reminder not only of Princess Dagmar's undeniable beauty but also her significant place within history.
